French designer and illustrator @jean_jullien has teamed up with @hatopress for a playful new publication affectionately poking fun at today’s holidaymakers and their blunders. If you’re feeling kinda chilly, you can warm up to more of Jean’s illustrations on the site right now. #itsnicethat #illustration

London studio @la_boca_ has carved out a niche for itself creating covers for books and records, and film posters that have gone on to win the independent London studio numerous industry accolades. See some more on the site right about now #itsnicethat #graphicdesign

On the site today Photographer Sophie Green chats to us about spontaneity, process and her latest series about traveller culture. "I wouldn’t want to take pictures that compromise the integrity of the person I’m shooting. It’s important to honour and respect their lives and show them fairly.” #itsnicethat #photography @sophiegreenstudio

For the last five years Austria-based studio OrtnerSchinko has created posters for a monthly club night in the city of Linz. Over 50 posters have been created for The Future Sound, but what’s striking about them is how cohesive they are as a series. You can get a good look on the site right now. #itsnicethat #graphicdesign

Illustrator @AnnaKovecses has applied her minimalist style to a fantastic series for The New York Times Magazine, recreating medical cases from the past in a straightforward, but creative manner. See some more of her work the site today. #itsnicethat #illustration

Janet Delaney captured New York city in the 1980s but rather than the big landmarks and tourist spots, the photographer focused on the people that dwell within its lofty buildings and busy streets. See more of the series on the site this weekend. #itsnicethat #photography

From Warhol's Wild Raspberries to the Private World of Pablo Picasso, creative director of Clash magazine Rob Meyers shared his favourite books with us this week. Go check it out if you're feeling nosy. #itsnicethat

Istanbul-based @hosgorselman pairs famous contemporaries like Picasso and Dali in his latest series of collages. The Central Saint Martins graduate also experiments with making some of his images move. So if you pop over to the site, they'll wink at you and everything. #itsnicethat #collage
Art as a human right and why creativity is being “pushed out of” London: we meet with Bob and Roberta Smith. Read all about it on the site this weekend. #itsnicethat

Photographer Brandon Tauszik (@be_dizzle) has focused on the barber shops of Oakland, California, in his series Tapered Throne. Choosing to shoot with video over photography, his images come to life as subtle gifs to allow for a "deeper connection between the subject and the view that still photography might not have accomplished.” #itsnicethat

In the final edition of our workwear series, we visited GQ Style’s fashion director Elgar Johnson. “I reference everything from my past. I don’t think I could do anything that I wasn’t around for because I don’t think it’s honest.” Read the full interview on the site right about now. #itsnicethat #fashion (photography @elliotjameskennedy)

Switzerland's @a3studio produce bold typographic work with bright patterns and deconstructed forms. The studio also exhibits its work and has received design awards, particularly for its poster work. Go get an eyeful on the site. #itsnicethat #graphicdesign

Canadian artist @scottsueme’s latest series of paintings have a sporty theme from swimming pools to concrete playgrounds. Focusing on unusual angles or honing in on the abstract details allows Scott to provide an alternative perspective of these typically active places. See some more on the site right now. #itsnicethat #art

Simple geometric forms and cutesy pastel palettes belie the serious undertones in some of graphic designer Cecilia Serafini’s work. See more of Cecilia's beautiful print and poster creations on the site right now. #itsnicethat #graphicdesign

The cover of our next issue of Printed Pages went to print yesterday. We can’t reveal it to you of course, that would ruin all the fun, but rest assured it’s bloody brilliant and you’ll be able to get your hands on it in November. #itsnicethat #printedpages

Photographer @LandonNordeman offers a slightly outsider perspective on fashion week reportage. The result is a refreshing departure from the from the endless run-of-the-mill shots of the catwalk. See more of his fantastic shots on the site right now. #itsnicethat #photography

French studio My Name is Wendy consistently produces strong, striking and interesting design and this series of posters celebrating the work of Stéphane Mallarmé is no exception to the rule. You can see the full series on the site right about now. #itsnicethat #graphicdesign

This beautiful beast of a design book landed in the studio yesterday. Over 6000 brand trademarks drawn from the years 1940-1980. If you fancy seeing some other things we like, along with what goes down in the It's Nice That / INT Works studio, you can follow @21downhamroad. Lovely stuff. #itsnicethat #21downhamroad

French studio @violaineetjeremy was recently tasked with designing a bright new identity for Paris’ Le Théâtre des Bouffes du Nord. The identity sees fonts Nord and Sud – which have a thoroughly old Paris feel – sit against abstract splashes of ink and bleeding watercolour. See more on the site right now. #itsnicethat #graphicdesign

“I make art for history. Not for someone, but for a time or space, which is the contribution to the history of art. That’s the thing I get off on.” On the site today we have a chat with conceptual artist Ryan Gander. #itsnicethat #ryangander (photography by @lindabrownlee)
